<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/240</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">12 March, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: This note seems to me
                            thorough and satisfactory,<note n="6" xml:id="d233fn1">
                                <ref target="frus1915#pg_105">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, p.
                                105</ref>.</note> and I hope that it may be possible to despatch it
                            promptly.</p>
                        <p>I have suggested a few verbal changes.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>